HEADWORD: Theave
<hw>Theave</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. W.
<ets>dafad</ets> a sheep, ewe.]</ety> <def>A ewe lamb of the first year;
also, a sheep three years old.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>thave</asp>.]</altsp> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>
<rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
